THABANG Moswane who is accused of murdering his mum remains in custody. The 24-year-old from Mathopestad Village near Koster appeared in the Koster Magistrates Court on Monday, 1 August. The case has been transferred to the Koster Regional Court, where Moswane will appear on 6 September. He was arrested in May for allegedly stabbing his 53-year-old mother to death and was allegedly seen drinking her blood from the stabbed wound on her neck by his twin brother. Moswane looked very calm in his red overall coat. He seemed to have hoped to see his family as he kept looking around. It is alleged that he and his mother, Kedisaletse Moswane, had an argument after he asked for R10 and she did not have it. The mother of six was found dead with numerous stab wounds. THABANG Moswane who is accused of murdering his mum remains in custody. The 24-year-old from Mathopestad Village near Koster appeared before the Koster Magistrates Court on Monday, 1 August. The case has been transferred to the Koster Regional Court. Moswane will make his appearance on the 6 September 2022. Moswane was arrested in May for allegedly stabbing his 53-year-old mother to death and was allegedly seen drinking her blood from the stabbed wound on her neck by his twin brother. Moswane looked very calm in his red overall coat. He seemed to have hoped to see his family as he kept looking around. It alleged that Thabang and his mother, Kedisaletse Moswane, had an argument after Thabang asked for a R10 and Kedisaletse did not have it. The mother of six was found dead with numerous stab wounds.